 Russian Doll Envelopes

ğŸ“ Problem Statement

You are given a list of envelopes.
Each envelope has width and height: (w, h)
You can put an envelope into another only if:

w1 < w2 AND h1 < h2

Find the maximum number of envelopes that can be nested (Russian doll style).


---

ğŸ” Example

Input:

[[5,4], [6,4], [6,7], [2,3]]

Output:

3

Explanation:

(2,3) â†’ (5,4) â†’ (6,7)


---

ğŸ’¡ Approach (Optimal)

1ï¸âƒ£ Sort envelopes by:

width ascending

if width same â†’ height descending


2ï¸âƒ£ Take only heights
3ï¸âƒ£ Find Longest Increasing Subsequence (LIS) in heights
4ï¸âƒ£ LIS length = answer âœ”


---

ğŸ§  Why descending height when same width?

To avoid wrongly counting envelopes with same width as valid nestings.

Example:

(6,4) and (6,7) cannot nest because width same




â± Complexity

Type	Value

Time	O(n log n)
Space	O(n)
